4.3. QuantiÔ¨Åcation of DiÔ¨Äerential Co-Expression
To focus on pairs of genes with diÔ¨Äerential co-expression, and to remove false positives composed of diÔ¨Äerences that are univariate, we removed genes where diÔ¨Äerences between sensitive and resistant groups were driven
mostly by a single gene. To this end, we applied Mann-Whitney U non-parametric test, and excluded genes with
p-value below 0.05. Similarly, we discarded genes where the diÔ¨Äerences between classes were not in average
expression levels, but instead there was large diÔ¨Äerence in expression variance, or in within-class ranges of expression. For this task, we employed the Levene non-parametric test, and Ô¨Åltered out genes with p-value below
0.05.
Next, we estimated Pearson correlation coeÔ¨Écient for samples from drug sensitive and drug resistant groups
separately, obtaining coeÔ¨Écients r1 and r2 . We then applied the Fisher‚Äôs Z transformation [28] to the coeÔ¨Écients
to obtain a test statistic z:
